  <title translate="true">SWI2: Seawater Intrusion Package</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">SWI2: Seawater Intrusion Package</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">SWI2: Seawater Intrusion Package </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Features_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Features</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab of the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Object_Properties_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Object Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box. This pane is only visible if the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SWI2_Seawater_Intrusion_Packag" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">SWI</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> package is selected &#160;and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SWI2_Seawater_Intrusion_Packag" anchor="ISWIOBS" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">SWI Observations</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is set to either binary or ASCII. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">SWI2: Seawater Intrusion Package </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">pane is used to define observations for either UCODE or PEST. If </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Pest_Properties_Basic_Pane" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">PEST is activated</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, the observation data will be processed using </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Mf2005ObsExtractor" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Mf2005ObsExtractor</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. Otherwise it will be processed with SwiObsExtractor.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The observations are defined similarly to how other observations for UCODE are defined. You must specify an observation name, time, Zeta (the observed value), Statistic, and StatFlag. For PEST, the statistic will be converted to a weight based on the choice of StatFlag. The observation must also specify the Zeta surface to which the observation(s) apply. ModelMuse will create an instruction file for post-processing with either </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Mf2005ObsExtractor" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Mf2005ObsExtractor</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or SwiObsExtractor. The postprocessor will interpolate in space and time to the location and time of the observation to generate a corresponding simulated value. The interpolation is done in the same way as head observations are interpolated in space and time in MODFLOW-2005. </text></para>
  </body>
